meaningMnemonic: A <kanji>withdrawal</kanji> is something you do to remove something from the <kanji>past</kanji>. It is a <vocabulary>withdrawal</vocabulary> or <vocabulary>removal</vocabulary> of what you did or submitted before.
readingMnemonic: This is a jukugo word that uses the on'yomi readings of the kanji. You should be able to read this on your own. Look out for the shortened てつ.
